'''Si̍t-kuk''' (矽谷, [[Yîn-ngî]]: Silicon Valley), he [[Kô Khô-kî]] sṳ-ngia̍p yùn-si̍p ke [[Mî-koet]] [[Kâ-chû]] [[Santa Clara Kuk]] ke phe̍t-chhṳ̂n, vi-yî [[Kâ-li-fuk-nì-â]] pet-phu, [[Khiu-kîm-sân]] vân-khî nàm-phu; yit-pân pâu-hàm Santa Clara khiùn lâu tûng [[Khiu-kîm-sân Vân-khî]] ke [[Fremont-sṳ]]. Chui-chó he [[ngiên-kiu]] lâu sâng-sán [[Si̍t]] chok-vi kî-chhú ke [[pan-thô-thí chin-phién]] ke thi-fông. [[Mî-koet]] lâu sṳ-kie khì-thâ kô-sîn kî-su̍t-khî tû-chhai put-thon fat-chán chong-thai, than-he Si̍t-kuk yìn-yèn he [[Kô Khô-kî]] [[kî-su̍t]] chhóng-sîn lâu fat-chán ke khôi-chhóng-chá, liá-ke thi-khî ke chhóng-ngia̍p thèu-chṳ̂ chiam-hi chhiòn Mî-koet chhóng-ngia̍p thèu-chṳ̂ chúng-ngiak ke sâm fûn chṳ̂-yit.
